data.meta_description: Jun 10, 2013 - The Resplendent Quetzal (Pharomachrus mocinno) is found from southern Mexico to western Panama (unlike the other quetzals of the genus Pharomachrus, which are found in South America and eastern Panama).This quetzal plays an important role in Mesoamerican mythologies. The Resplendent Quetzal is Guatemala's national bird, and an image of it is on the flag and coat of arms of Guatemala. It is also the name of the local currency. See more ideas about quetzal, bird, beautiful birds.
